<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>People here love to shit on Ubuntu mentioning Canonical&#39;s growing impact of Microsoft, decision to use snaps over flatpaks or appimages etc etc.</p> <p>You understand the point however the reason Ubuntu is most widely used Linux distribution is because (also the reason people like me are using it since we used it first)</p> <ol> <li> Things work in Ubuntu (Bluetooth, WiFi, cameras) etc.</li> <li> All daily driver apps support Ubuntu officially or in small ase unofficially.</li> <li> It is as stable as Debian while providing latest security and apps ecosystem.</li> <li> It is neat and does not come with features which do not work the way user expects (Looking at you MS search bar)</li> <li> Bundled with KDE, you got yourself the best of experience from Windows and Mac OS.</li> </ol> <p>No finger pointing to other Linux distros but Ubuntu is the reason I have felt at home at Linux and KDE.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/youareafakenews"> /u/youareafakenews </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/13h863r/ubuntu_is_the_reason_i_love_linux/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/13h863r/ubuntu_is_the_reason_i_love_linux/">[comments]</a></span>